Hey, %playername%, I'm getting really cold,░ I'll see you tomorrow 'kay?

Events.Text: Go get back in the bath!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Thanks,░ I'll seeya %playername%!
<i>*Click*

Events.Text:

Perfectly good bed over there,░ but you were in the middle of a Nextflix marathon.

Say, who was that you were chatting with?░ Found a hotty at the bar last night?

Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text:
Yeah not exactly.░ 
But thanks mom, you were right... getting out there was kind of fun.░ Did you meet anyone nice?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yeah,░ I did actually!░ I was thinking about calling one of th-░ I mean the one guy and see if he'd like to meet up again today.░ Tall and really funny,░ you'd like him!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: Sounds like a character alright.░ Well I'll let you have shower priority,░ and I'll clean up the place just incase I do end up bringing someone home.░ I'm going to need to move some of your old posters.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I like those posters!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: Yeah but they aren't exactly appropriate,░ she might think they're mine,░ and that I have a bizarre obsession with men's junk.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Like she would care.░ I didn't hear any complaints earlier!░ I think it's cute.
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: What's cute?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: That you're already considering bringing her home and making a good impression.
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: You're hilarious.░ Anyway I've got some errands to run,░ let me know how things with Mr. Suave goes, okay?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Same to you!░ I want to know more about this girl when you get home!░ See you when I get out of the shower!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: <i>Glad thats over.░ Even if this meet-up tomorrow doesn't go anywhere,░ it's still a good opportunity to get some stuff done today.░ I'm surprised we managed to get the room into the state that it's in...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Today felt longer than usual.░ I guess I've just been used to the same routine,░ never having to worry about anything much besides myself and keeping up with a few friends.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Perhaps that club was the kickstart I needed to get back on track...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>*BEEP*░ *BEEP*░ *BEEP*░ *Click*

That alarm never ceases to be annoying.░ I slept better than I expected.░ I can't say the anticipation of hanging out with Skye doesn't have me a little excited.

Yeah! 
Do you use Scrape or Riscord? What about Telegraph?

Hey, so was that all you wanted to ask?

Events.Text:
<i>To be honest it makes me wonder just how many of these outfits and characters she has done in the past.░
If she always dresses a little skimpily,░ I may just take a liking to this hobby...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Are there any other video game characters you've done costumes for? Anyone I'd know?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
I only recently got into video games, so this will be my second game character.░ I've been cosplaying for a few years now,░ some of the more complicated characters take a while gathering foam and material to make the accessories.
Mostly I based it off of animes,░ you know... Japanese cartoons?
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: So, do you tailor all that yourself?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yep! I have a sewing machine at home,░ my room is usually covered in pieces of my next project.░ This one I can probably finish super quick though,░ since it's mainly just making my fur look right.
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: Have you ever messed up when using dyes?░ I would have a hell of a time trying to use more than one color.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Oh yeah that can totally happen.░ You learn from trial and error how to keep your colors separated.░ This one time I was trying to look like a character that had both yellow and blue in her fur.░ I ended up looking like pea soup.
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: It's easy to wash out though,░ so don't be scared off from trying it!
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: I'll leave the crazy colours to you for now.░ Did you still want to look around here some more or...?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yeah, I'm probably driving you nuts with my rambling.░ Let's go check out some other stores!
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text:
<i>I noticed the younger customers at the game store were getting a kick out of her attire,░ One of the youngest commented to his mother that he recognized her from his favourite cartoon.░
I also catch the attention of two older boys,░ whispering to each other and making gestures her way: they stopped quickly when they saw that I'd noticed.░ Luckily Skye didn't seem to see them... I guess being showy has good and bad sides.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We walked around a while, peaking in at the gadget store and trading a few music recommendations outside the music store before waving it off and realizing we could probably just send a Viewtube link to the artists after the date.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>She would go quiet as they passed,░ her arms tightly folded beneath her bust,░ waiting for them to be at a certain distance before picking up the conversation again.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>In the few moments we had the walkway to ourselves,░ she would hop and skip to the pace of my steps.░ Children didn't seem to bother her,░ she approached them willingly and greeted them in a playful way when they recognized her character.░ I guess that was part of the show though...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Skye was a window shopper.░ Every time we passed a clothing store she would take two steps back to quickly peer through the glass.░ She always caught back up to me before I could ask whether she wanted to go inside and would just shake her head and smile when I offered.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Oh my god,░ I love milkshakes!░ I'd kinda tried to avoid the store because,░ you know... they don't let you go into the fabric store with a drink...░ You didn't have to pay for it y'know!
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: It's cool!░ Just make sure you save me a little.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Already swapping saliva are we?░ Heh, I'll save you some...░ Hey can we check out Foxy?░ They have really nice shorts and tops there,░ I'll trade you lame clothes shopping for the rest of the milshake?
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: Is that where you got the daisy dukes?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Actually these were my old skinny jeans.░ My friends told me they would look great as shorts,░ so I used my sewing kit to reduce the length of the legs.░ Over time I just kept modding them because everyone likes them shorter!
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: Well, I think they suit you!░ Hopefully you'll give that friend my thanks?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Har har!░ But thanks, %playername%/...░ I get what you mean,░ my parents already don't like them how they look now.░ But I'm not gonna get started on my parents,░ they aren't really big fans of my cosplay either so they can just deal with it.░ Who knows,░ maybe we'll find you something in here too!

Events.Text: Clothes shopping is so much fun.░ This place is kinda expensive cause the brand is a really popular one,░ I even see the occasional guy wearing this stuff!
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: Yeah I was gonna say,░ I don't really see a men's section here yet. Is it mostly girl's clothes?

Events.Text: See,░ that's the trick!░ It's a girls' clothing store.░ There's some unisex stuff,░ you just gotta look for it.

Events.Text: <i>At least no one seems to be ogling her here.░ The only other customers here were preoccupied with their own shopping.░ She let me have the milkshake, occasionally leaning in to steal a little back as we wandered the store.░ Skye bobbed her body to the music,░ it was a poppy song that has been playing everywhere recently, but her energy about it was infectious.

Events.Text: Anything catching your eye so far?
Events.Title: %playername%

Skye.░

%playername%, can we go to the other side of the store now?

Events.Text: <i>The back and forth between the three was getting out of hand.░ I may have been able to shrug off  their usual bitchiness when it was aimed at me,░ but Skye was beginning to turn red.░ I quickly took her hand and tried to steer her away from the conversation.

<i>The girls rolled their eyes and laughed,░ feeding off of Skye's outburst.░ Her loud cursing was heard by the other shoppers in the store,░ turning heads.░
I have to diffuse the situation before I end up with a cat fight on my hands.

I'm really sorry you got dragged into that, Skye.░
I honestly can't stand them either,░ they're just two stupid bitches from my high school year.░ They act that way to everybody trust me.

I don't know why they'd be so mean though... I didn't even do anything to them...░
Is it because they saw me with you?

Events.Text: No way,░ it's probably just their way of continuing to tease me... Their opinion doesn't mean anything to me. And,░ seriously,░ it shouldn't mean anything to you either. At the best, I think they were jealous.
Events.Title: %playername%

Oh god, I'm so stupid...░
I'm sorry, I don't do the whole dating thing very often and here I am showing off clothes shopping with you...

Events.Text: Everyone does that,░ they were just trying to make us feel bad, Skye.░ Seriously, I didn't think you were trying to show off.░ If anything you went off to look at the more risque things without me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Fine... But, you don't think I look slutty in this,░ do you?
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: In their defence,░ even the guys in the game store where commenting on how high cut your shorts were...░ I guess those kinds of clothes are going to cause all sorts of reactions?░ That's good and bad I guess? I think you look nice,░ but it's not exactly... subtle?

Events.Text: It's just that most of the characters I dress up as don't even wear clothes.░ I'm not dressing to flaunt stuff, but if I wanna show all the details I've done dying my fur I can't be totally conservative.░ I guess I'm just so used to encouragement from the cosplay community that I forgot people like that exist.
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text:
Not at all,░ don't let people like that dictate what you can or can't wear.░
If you feel comfortable wearing that stuff,░ then that's all that matters.░ There's not much point in dying fur if you don't show it off.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'm not trying to look like I wanna get into someone's pants though,░ it's just that most of the characters I dress up as don't even wear clothes.░ I finally get my fur looking just like it does in the show, I wanna show it off a little...░ I guess I'm just so used to encouragement from the cosplay community that I forgot people like that exist.
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text:
I'm sorry for yelling.░
I used to get teased by girls just like that back in school and it was a nasty reminder.░

Events.Text: Can we go find a nice place to have lunch and cool off?
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: Sounds like a plan.░ I know a guy down the block that makes the best shawarma.░ Have you tried one before?

Events.Text: <i>We both were so caught up in the moment that as Skye took a step through the scanners that gate the entrance to the store it started to bleep an alarm.░ Skye was jolted by the sudden noise,░ freezing mid step before we both realized what had happened.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Ugh,░ great! Can this day get any better or what?░ I forgot all about the new top...
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: Oh crap,░ my other clothes have been sitting in an open changeroom for, like, five minutes...
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text:
It's not like we're running off.░
I'm sure this kinda stuff happens all the time,░ and the store manager probably saw Lunar and Jackie giving you a hard time...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yeah, no kidding...░ Phew... Okay, I just need to calm down.░ I'll get changed and meet you back here?
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text:
Sounds good.░
I'll go over and make sure they know everything's fine while you change.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Thanks %playername%.░ I'm glad you're here...░
By the way,░ you never did answer my question.

Events.Text: About the outfit?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yeah,░ what do you think?
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: I think it looks good on you.░ It matches the rest of your outfit!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hehe, come on, 'it suits me'?░ You've gotta give me a little more than that.
Events.Title: Skye

Events.Text: It's very summery,░ I guess it makes more sense than a hoody to wear on a hot day like this!░ It looks like you're ready to go down to the beach or relax somewhere, it's very... fresh?

Events.Text: That's sort of what I was aiming for in a way!░ I guess my other outfit was kinda confused with the hoodie and all...

Events.Text: It looks great against the gold fur.░ You have an eye for picking out stuff that compliments colors!░ Foxy also seems to make some great stuff,░ and you make it work.

Events.Text: You think so?░ I picked it out having the colour blue in mind too, but I guess it works for this character too?░ You'll see what I mean later!

Events.Text: It shows off how well you've done up your fur,░ I think it's gonna look awesome when you portray your next character!

I guess you're right, gives me more freedom to do cool fur designs on the arms...░
You really like it,░ huh?░ Maybe I'll have to let you be the first to see my new costume.

'Foxy' is an understatement,░ I think you would look great in pretty much anything on display here.░
It really show off your figure in all the right ways!

I guess there's only one real way to find out,░ I should give her a call when I'm ready to head over...
At least I had the memento of the jacket for now,░ it smelled a little of Skye's perfume.░ I was sure to fold it up safe in my drawers so it didn't accidentally get washed, ruining the autograph.

Events.Text:
<i>I wasn't really sure what to expect when I pulled up,░ but the large convention center parking lot was packed with people,░ half of them seemed to be in costume!░
I wasn't exactly sure who some of them were,░ but a lot seemed based on classic video games,░ your Residents of E.Ville soldiers and Team Rock It costumes I knew, at least in passing.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey, that's not a big deal!░ I'm just glad your friends seemed so nice.░ I guess talking about their costumes is only natural when you're all dressed up for the con!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>I let my fingers play over her palm and she returned the gesture with a playful squeeze of my thumb.░
She seemed to come to her senses after a moment,░ shaking her blush free as she looked back down the line as the doors opened to the sales room.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Really? That's kinda lame...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>I ended up killing time around the booths,░ I even did end up picking up a new game, maybe something I could play with Skye later.░ 
I had to admit,░ the place wasn't quite as fun browsing around by myself,░ Skye's star-struck reactions to some of the more famous artists and voice actors was really part of the fun,░ though I guess if I'd known some of them I'd have had the same reaction.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I slipped away not long after Skye left, ░there was already a large crowd fighting over spots for the parade and it wasn't even going to start for a while.░ Skye was lovely,░ but I wasn't really feeling like getting shoved around for two hours just to take a few more photos of her,░ we'd already taken lots of photos during the day, after all.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>After an hour,░ I found a good strategic place to set up on a bend in the cosplay parade path where I'd get a good uninterrupted shot of the cosplayers.░ It took a little time standing there,░ some sort of hold up in the photo room,░ but eventually all manner of creative cosplayers started to make their way along the parade circuit.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It took a while for them to get to me,░ but Skye was right,░ it was pretty cool to see some of the more famous characters I knew brought to life by the cosplayers,░ especially the ones who threw in little gestures and pulled faces to act out their characters.░ I was sad to see that the parade was being led by the top five costumes and Lexy, Hane and Skye weren't among them.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Skye was there in the parade though,░ looking happy as ever,░ they had arranged the group into game genres and she was back with some of the other Brawn characters,░ throwing fake attacks at the audience and pretending to beef it out with the other cast members.░ As she passed she threw me a playful kiss and a wink before sauntering off,░ talk about a cute picture to remember the afternoon by,░ even if it was getting a little late.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>By the time the parade was done,░ the sun was starting to set,░ Skye insisted that I kept her jacket safe and brought it over the next time we hung out.░
We shared one last hug,░ hasty and interrupted by Skye getting a call from her parents to get a ride home.░ I promised I wouldn't keep her waiting too long on getting the jacket back to her.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The environment was better than I'd hoped,░ everyone was smiling, roaming together in groups of laughing friends between the panels and game rooms.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>The nerd community really was pretty open,░ so I guess I shouldn't have been that suprised,░ even if I hadn't been to this particular con.
It was cool to catch quite a few good cosplayers of some of the games and animes I knew,░ I'd definitely have to take a few photos myself!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
I had a couple idea of game characters I could cosplay, but I didn't have too much time.░ I thought about grabbing a Japanese school uniform or something,░ just to do something simple from an anime,░ but I wouldn't have had time to get the school insignia right.
That's not a problem right? I checked and there didn't seem to be any rules about cosplay-only areas and I figured I'd be coming in a bit late to wait in a prop line.
Events.Title: %playername%

Still, I'm really glad you made it!

Events.Text: <i>Putting two and two together,░ even if Skye's hoodie was a simple themed hoodie based on a super sentai anime,░ getting the signature of the voice actor for it would probably make it worth a pretty penny.░ The anime was pretty popular too.

No way! That's a pretty awesome score!░

Not that it wasn't an ego boost to see a few jealous faces as we walked by.

A couple of the people watching saw Skye's costume and gave another cheer.░ She cheered them on in return and gave them a few cutely ineffective shadow boxing moves.

Events.Text: Haha... So, are we gonna be boxing, or did you wanna go head-to-head on Brawn? I dunno how I feel about beating up the game Lucco with you dressed like that...

Come on!

If it kept up like this I could probably keep pace!

It was starting to get faster, but I think I was getting the rhythm!░

Events.Text: <i>Skye slipped out of the gaming room leaving me to follow.░ Jeeze... I guess I really messed that up...

I text Skye but she didn't reply... I guess this was a total bust,░ I should go home.

Events.Text:

Events.Text: <i>In the end I couldn't help but notice that I was getting just as many cheers as Skye was,░ even though she was in cosplay, and those cutely short shorts.░ I guess a perfect score does that, but I was honestly surprised,░ I was struggling to keep track myself with Skye laughing and dancing along.

Events.Text: <i>I might have been able to keep up with her,░ but Skye certainly handled it with more grace.░ I couldn't help but feel more like a herky-jerky puppet flailing my arms while Skye was throwing in kicks and arm movements to the songs.

Events.Text: <i>It helped that I knew some of the songs from their anime shows,░ maybe not well enough to sing along like some of the crowd were,░ not when I was trying to pay attention to the arrows░ and not being distracted by Skye dancing along to all the arm movements from the credits video.
